Russia's Foreign Intelligence Service has closed a tender for three research projects that aim to monitor blogs and social media and distribute a large amount of messages to shape public opinion, the daily publication Kommersant writes. [Russian]

Sluzhba Vneshney Razvedki, or Foreign Intelligence Service, is part of the Russian General Staff of the Armed Forces.

According to the report, the intelligence agency is funding the three projects to the tune of 30 million rubles ($900,000).❞

